<span id="v.iv.lxviii-p2"></span><span class="c12"><span
id="v.iv.lxviii-p2.1"></span>Isaac, <span
id="fr_2685"></span>[2686](#fn_2685.md) </span> presbyter of the church at
Antioch, whose many works cover a long period, wrote in Syriac
especially against the Nestorians and Eutychians. He lamented the
downfall of Antioch in an elegiac poem, taking up the same strain that
Ephraim, the deacon, sounded on the downfall of Nicomedia. He died
during the reign of Leo and Majorianus.

